cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new instance segmentation method for biological images, which involves object detection and segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method also involves the use of object features and normalization, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of RoI (region of interest) patches, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural network (cs.NE) research.
